
### 1. Reverse a String

**Problem:** Reverse a given string.

```java
class ReverseString {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String str = "hello";
        String rev = "";

        for (int i = str.length() - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
            rev += str.charAt(i);
        }
        System.out.println("Reversed string: " + rev);
    }
}
```

---

### 2. Check Palindrome String

**Problem:** Check whether a string is a palindrome.

```java
class PalindromeString {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String str = "madam";
        String rev = "";

        for (int i = str.length() - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
            rev += str.charAt(i);
        }

        if (str.equals(rev))
            System.out.println("Palindrome");
        else
            System.out.println("Not Palindrome");
    }
}
```

---

### 3. Count Vowels and Consonants

**Problem:** Count vowels and consonants in a string.

```java
class CountVowelsConsonants {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String str = "programming";
        int vowels = 0, consonants = 0;
        str = str.toLowerCase();

        for (int i = 0; i < str.length(); i++) {
            char ch = str.charAt(i);
            if (ch >= 'a' && ch <= 'z') {
                if (ch == 'a' || ch == 'e' || ch == 'i' || ch == 'o' || ch == 'u')
                    vowels++;
                else
                    consonants++;
            }
        }
        System.out.println("Vowels: " + vowels);
        System.out.println("Consonants: " + consonants);
    }
}
```

---

### 4. Count Characters in a String

**Problem:** Count total characters excluding spaces.

```java
class CountCharacters {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String str = "hello world";
        int count = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i < str.length(); i++) {
            if (str.charAt(i) != ' ')
                count++;
        }
        System.out.println("Character count: " + count);
    }
}
```

---

### 5. Find Duplicate Characters in a String

**Problem:** Print duplicate characters in a string.

```java
class DuplicateCharacters {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String str = "programming";
        char[] arr = str.toCharArray();

        for (int i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
            for (int j = i + 1; j < arr.length; j++) {
                if (arr[i] == arr[j] && arr[i] != ' ') {
                    System.out.println(arr[i]);
                    break;
                }
            }
        }
    }
}
```

---

### 6. Check Anagram Strings

**Problem:** Check if two strings are anagrams.

```java
import java.util.Arrays;

class AnagramCheck {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String str1 = "listen";
        String str2 = "silent";

        char[] a = str1.toCharArray();
        char[] b = str2.toCharArray();

        Arrays.sort(a);
        Arrays.sort(b);

        if (Arrays.equals(a, b))
            System.out.println("Anagram");
        else
            System.out.println("Not Anagram");
    }
}
```

---

### 7. Find First Non-Repeated Character

**Problem:** Find the first non-repeated character in a string.

```java
class FirstNonRepeatedChar {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String str = "swiss";

        for (int i = 0; i < str.length(); i++) {
            boolean unique = true;
            for (int j = 0; j < str.length(); j++) {
                if (i != j && str.charAt(i) == str.charAt(j)) {
                    unique = false;
                    break;
                }
            }
            if (unique) {
                System.out.println("First non-repeated character: " + str.charAt(i));
                break;
            }
        }
    }
}
```

